          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "ESTRG"
                ],
                "institute": "1USADKE"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " High Intensity Gamma Source (HIgS)",
                "Facility on the campus of Duke University."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "LCS"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A high-flux photon beam is created by colliding",
                "relativistic electron beam bunches, circulating in a",
                "storage ring, with photon pulses inside the",
                "high-power optical cavity of a free-electron laser",
                " (FEL). The average electron beam current and energy",
                "were 100 mA and 623 MeV, respectively. The FEL photon",
                "wavelength was 546.5 nm, which resulted in a",
                "13.0+0.22-0.25 MeV photon beam. The photon beam was",
                "shaped upstream of the 238U target using an aluminum",
                "collimator of length 44.5 cm with a circular hole of",
                "1.90 cm in diameter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE",
                "NAICR",
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The photon beam energy spectrum",
                "was measured with a 110% coaxial high-purity germanium",
                " (HPGe) detector and a large cylindrical (25 cm",
                "diameter x 35 cm length) NaI detector, both of which",
                "were positioned in the beam path downstream of the",
                "target irradiation location."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "92-U-238",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.99974
              },
              "free_text": [
                " In order to determine the total",
                "fission rate in the thick 238U activation target, the",
                "measured fission rate in the DFC is scaled by the mass",
                "ratio of the thin-to-thick 238U targets. Both the thick",
                " and thin targets are 1.27 cm in diameter. Masses and",
                "isotopic purity of the 238U target and reference foils",
                "installed in the dual fission chamber (DFC).",
                "Foil       Mass                  Isotopic purity (%)",
                "DFC 1      124.3(16) microg      99.998",
                "DFC 2      136.7(18) microg      99.998",
                "Target     441.0(1)  mg          99.974"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The fission rate in the target is determined",
                "from in-beam measurements made using a dual fission",
                "chamber (DFC) containing thin foils of the same nucleus",
                " of which the 238U target is made. Short-lived FPYs",
                "were measured by performing cyclic activation of the",
                "sample using a rapid target transfer system.",
                "Following activation, the 238U target was rapidly",
                " (0.4 s) transferred to a counting station consisting",
                "of two well-shielded high-purity germanium detectors.",
                "The irradiation-counting cycle was repeated until the",
                "summed data had sufficient statistical accuracy."
              ]
            }
          ],
